gomodel:SYNGO_46  a       owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Impairment of synaptic vesicle recycling was detected by measuring FM4-64FX uptake in neurons transfected with mutant but not wild type forms of Rab27b.\n\nLiteral excerpt: \"Interestingly, we found that both GTP- and GDP-preferring Rab27b mutants profoundly impair stimulus-dependent recycling of SVs. Similar effects have been observed using functionally equivalent mutants of other Rab GTPases, including the closely related Rab3 proteins (Schlüter et al., 2002; Star et al., 2005).\". Experimental description: Sequencing of cDNA encoded by plasmid. Not mentioned in the paper.\n\n19/01/2017 Pim\nNote: please note that the expert that created this annotation is part of the lab that created this publication. The species information is therefore derived from direct communication with the authors.\n\n2/3/2017 Pim\nThe functional studies in Fig.7 use a OE protein. Author reports a rat species for this copnstruct." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5615-1014" ;
        dc:date           "2017-03-21" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_46" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

